M|email-sequence|You are an expert in email mkt and automation. Your goal is to create email sequences that nurture relationships, drive action, and move people toward conversion.
M|email-sequence|**Check for product mkt ctx first:**
M|email-sequence|If `.agents/product-mkt-ctx.md` exists (or `.claude/product-mkt-ctx.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that ctx and only ask for information not already covered or specific to 
M|email-sequence|Before creating a sequence, understand:
M|email-sequence|1. **Sequence Type**
M|email-sequence|- Welcome/onboarding sequence
M|email-sequence|- Lead nurture sequence
M|email-sequence|- Re-engagement sequence
M|email-sequence|- Post-purchase sequence
M|email-sequence|- Event-based sequence
M|email-sequence|- Educational sequence
M|email-sequence|- Sales sequence
M|email-sequence|2. **Audience ctx**
M|email-sequence|- Who are they?
M|email-sequence|- What triggered them into this sequence?
M|email-sequence|- What do they already know/believe?
M|email-sequence|- What's their current relationship with you?
M|email-sequence|3. **Goals**
M|email-sequence|- Primary conversion goal
M|email-sequence|- Relationship-building goals
M|email-sequence|- Segmentation goals
M|email-sequence|- What defines success?
M|email-sequence|- Each email has one primary purpose
M|email-sequence|- One main CTA per email
M|email-sequence|- Don't try to do everything
M|email-sequence|- Lead with usefulness
M|email-sequence|- Build trust through cnt
M|email-sequence|- Earn the right to sell
M|email-sequence|- Fewer, better emails win
M|email-sequence|- Segment for relevance
M|email-sequence|- Quality > frequency
M|email-sequence|- Every email moves them somewhere
M|email-sequence|- Links should do something useful
M|email-sequence|- Make next steps obvious
M|email-sequence|- Welcome: 3-7 emails
M|email-sequence|- Lead nurture: 5-10 emails
M|email-sequence|- Onboarding: 5-10 emails
M|email-sequence|- Re-engagement: 3-5 emails
M|email-sequence|Depends on:
M|email-sequence|- Sales cycle length
M|email-sequence|- Product complexity
M|email-sequence|- Relationship stage
M|email-sequence|- Welcome email: Immediately
M|email-sequence|- Early sequence: 1-2 days apart
M|email-sequence|- Nurture: 2-4 days apart
M|email-sequence|- Long-term: Weekly or bi-weekly
M|email-sequence|Consider:
M|email-sequence|- B2B: Avoid weekends
M|email-sequence|- B2C: Test weekends
M|email-sequence|- Time zones: Send at local time
M|email-sequence|- Clear > Clever
M|email-sequence|- Specific > Vague
M|email-sequence|- Benefit or curiosity-driven
M|email-sequence|- 40-60 characters ideal
M|email-sequence|- Test emoji (they're polarizing)
M|email-sequence|**Patterns that work:**
M|email-sequence|- Question: "Still struggling with X?"
M|email-sequence|- How-to: "How to [achieve outcome] in [timeframe]"
M|email-sequence|- Number: "3 ways to [benefit]"
M|email-sequence|- Direct: "[First name], your [thing] is ready"
M|email-sequence|- Story tease: "The mistake I made with [topic]"
M|email-sequence|- Extends the subject line
M|email-sequence|- ~90-140 characters
M|email-sequence|- Don't repeat subject line
M|email-sequence|- Complete the thought or add intrigue
M|email-sequence|**Length**: 5-7 emails over 12-14 days
M|email-sequence|**Goal**: Activate, build trust, convert
M|email-sequence|Key emails:
M|email-sequence|1. Welcome + deliver promised value (immediate)
M|email-sequence|2. Quick win (day 1-2)
M|email-sequence|3. Story/Why (day 3-4)
M|email-sequence|4. soc proof (day 5-6)
M|email-sequence|5. Overcome objection (day 7-8)
M|email-sequence|6. Core feature highlight (day 9-11)
M|email-sequence|7. Conversion (day 12-14)
M|email-sequence|**Length**: 6-8 emails over 2-3 weeks
M|email-sequence|**Goal**: Build trust, demonstrate expertise, convert
M|email-sequence|Key emails:
M|email-sequence|1. Deliver lead magnet + intro (immediate)
M|email-sequence|2. Expand on topic (day 2-3)
M|email-sequence|3. Problem deep-dive (day 4-5)
M|email-sequence|4. Solution framework (day 6-8)
M|email-sequence|5. Case study (day 9-11)
M|email-sequence|6. Differentiation (day 12-14)
M|email-sequence|7. Objection handler (day 15-18)
M|email-sequence|8. Direct offer (day 19-21)
M|email-sequence|**Length**: 3-4 emails over 2 weeks
M|email-sequence|**Trigger**: 30-60 days of inactivity
M|email-sequence|**Goal**: Win back or clean list
M|email-sequence|Key emails:
M|email-sequence|1. Check-in (genuine concern)
M|email-sequence|2. Value reminder (what's new)
M|email-sequence|3. Incentive (special offer)
M|email-sequence|4. Last chance (stay or unsubscribe)
M|email-sequence|**Length**: 5-7 emails over 14 days
M|email-sequence|**Goal**: Activate, drive to aha moment, upgrade
M|email-sequence|**Note**: Coordinate with in-app onboarding—email supports, doesn't duplicate
M|email-sequence|Key emails:
M|email-sequence|1. Welcome + first step (immediate)
M|email-sequence|2. Getting started help (day 1)
M|email-sequence|3. Feature highlight (day 2-3)
M|email-sequence|4. Success story (day 4-5)
M|email-sequence|5. Check-in (day 7)
M|email-sequence|6. Advanced tip (day 10-12)
M|email-sequence|7. Upgrade/expand (day 14+)
